ThinkGeek.com, the number one destination in the galaxy for fascinating products and unique gifts that appeal to the geek community, is hiring a MySQL Database Administrator (DBA) to be responsible for maintaining and designing databases and troubleshooting related database code.<br />
<br />
<strong>Responsibilities </strong></p>
<p>
The DBA will work as part of the larger engineering team that produces custom solutions for our internal business units as well as the ThinkGeek.com e-commerce platform.&nbsp; This requires working closely with the Perl development and the technology operations team.&nbsp; Daily duties include system monitoring, database backup/recovery, and performance tuning. You will also participate in designing new database schemas and creation of different types of database objects. You will be responsible for database capacity planning, performance tuning and creation of database maintenance plans.</p>
<p>
<strong>Education &amp; Experience Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in computer science MIS, CIS, or related field or combination of work experience is required</li>
