<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Expert in SQL query language</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Extensive experience with database management/monitoring, clustering, ETL operations, query performance tuning and optimization</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with DB management in a high-transaction, high-availability environment is required.</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience supporting customer facing web applications a plus but not required.</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In depth knowledge of MySQL replication management and monitoring is required</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with Percona 5.5, mod_perl, and report creation are all plusses</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exposure to other RDBMS including MS SQL and Oracle are a plus.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent organizational skills with the ability to achieve results within tight deadlines</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MySQL certification is a plus</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advanced knowledge of MySQL and InnoDB internals</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assisting Software Engineering team with database related technical issues</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participating on application development projects, focusing on the transition of projects from Software Engineering to Production Infrastructure by addressing database activities within the software development life-cycle</li>
</ul>
<p>
