Geeknet, which owns and manages ThinkGeek.com, is looking for an enthusiastic, motivated Finance Intern to work with a fun, close-knit team and learn/do something new every day. As Geeknet&rsquo;s Finance Intern, you will support the Controller, the Financial Planning and Analysis team, and the rest of Finance as needed in a growing public company. You will increase your Finance and Accounting skills with practical experience by performing expense analysis, and assisting with Accounts Payable accounting, monthly closing activities and Fixed Asset inventory.</p>
